				\begin{document}$$\eta $$\end{document} increases due to higher surface area being available for dye adsorption [9][13][17]. Both parameters peak at an optimum thickness near which maximum output power is achieved [2]. Beyond the optimum thickness, values of the parameters declined as injected electrons become lost to more traps since transport distance is longer. Series resistance along the DSSC stack also increases, slightly reducing open-circuit voltage, VOC [15][17].

